parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in the vehicle running out of fuel, stalling, or leaving the driver stranded. This can be a serious safety hazard, especially if it occurs on a highway or in a remote area.
symptoms: The fuel gauge fluctuates wildly
showing empty or full randomly
the check engine light comes on
the fuel level sensor circuit is intermittent
the fuel gauge does not return to its normal position
the fuel gauge sticks to empty or full
the vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel.
